een making a clearer shift from index investments to active trading stock market regulation has increased in addition new investment products continuously demand more from information systems to manage securities etera has used solutions from the digia financial systems product family since the end of the ’s before then an inhouse system took care of debenture investment assets with the arrival of equity investments and the euro a more powerful comprehensive system was needed data more uptodate the installed system is used to handle etera’s investment asset backoffice functions from logging transactions to reporting and bookkeeping asset item values are monitored daily securities investments are divided into equity investments derivatives money market instruments and debentures information required for bookkeeping goes straight to bookkeeping account balancing has its own interface report drafting can be automated using report manager – reports can be chosen to meet official or inhouse bookkeeping requirements in autumn  the bloomberg market information service was integrated into the package as an outsourced service this provides closing prices of shares valuation reports key figures and risk evaluations plus information on company developments such as stock splits and share issues as a result information is much more up to date before some data had to be fetched manually from multiple sources digia values being involved in developing systems that boost the customers’ business automation continues “new investment products are appearing all the time especially for the derivatives markets growing risks requires moreactive monitoring of the markets real time information is the markets’ alpha and omega information is continually being analysed and combined more flexibly this line of work would be hard to imagine without a full reliable information system” explains maarit javanainen who is in charge of managing etera’s securities “i believe that automation will continue” “the stock markets are very lively naturally at digia we value being involved in developing systems that boost our customers’ business in a fastmoving environment” affirms tommi flink a director at digia customer stories food industry wholesale trade enterprise resource planning mpmaustepalvelu product traceability is the key to trust customer stories enterprise resource planning microsoft isoworks erp streamlines processes and practices customer stories wholesale trade enterprise resource planning enterprise crm microsoft orient occident business development presents new challenges to it ndash erp and crm in key position näytä lisää tuloksia back to top contact us × contact us contact information  etera suomeksi   på svenska etera in brief become a customer shop call ask us »   ​​insurance for selfemployed persons yel as an entrepreneur you must arrange your pension cover according to the selfemployed persons pensions act yel request for a quotationemployees’ pension insurance tyel employers arrange for statutory earningsrelated pension insurance for their employees  request for a quotation   ​customer service​employers and entrepreneurs ​weekdays from am to pmcu​stomer service office     or ​    ​employees ​weekdays from  am to  pm​pension information service​    or      ​information about pension record ​   or     ​vocational rehabilitationweekdays from  am to  noon​    or     ​» contact information   do you need assistance our customer service is here for you weekdays from  am –  pm     asiakaspalvelueterafi leave a contact request or send us a message my matter concerns tyel insurance for employees yel insurance for the selfemployed pension matters insurance services earningsrelated pension record vocational rehabilitation real estate communications you may enter either your phone number or your email address send name is missing erroneous phone number erroneous email address enter either a phone number or an email address thank you for your message well come